    "caption": "The desert's smallest fox, with the universe's biggest ears.",
    "shortDescription": "Fennec foxes are the tiniest wild dogs on Earth, but their ears are comically enormous — almost as long as their whole face — and they can swivel each ear separately to pinpoint a beetle rustling under the sand. They live in the Sahara and don't need to drink water at all, getting everything they need from food. Fun fact: A fennec fox's huge ears are lined with blood vessels that release heat and keep the animal cool in temperatures that would cook most creatures."
